We are looking for a self-motivated and talentedSr. EmployeeCommunications Manager to join our team. In this position, you will be producing high-quality content thatinforms, motivates, andengagesouremployees. 
The ideal candidate will have a blend ofinternalcommunications, storytelling,and program management experience.They should be an organized self-starter with a strong bias for action, passionate aboutgoal setting, continuous process improvement, delivering results, and be willing to roll-up their sleeves to contribute ideas, customize solutions, and positivelyinfluence the employee experience within the organization. 
Responsibilities 
Lead our end-to-end employee communication and engagement strategy, evolving our channels from a mix that has grown organically to a thoughtfully curated collection designed for impact. 
Write internal articles,messages, briefing documents,scripts,newsletter copy, and other campaign content as needed. 
Identify, recommend,andimplement creative methods for communicating with employees through a variety of channels, including, but not limited to, social platforms,listening and feedback systems,intranet, podcasts, videos, presentations, newsletters, all hands meetings, and emails. 
Storyboard and work withacreative teamto execute on various campaigns. 
Respond toemployeecommunication-related issues in a timely manner. 
Manage an organization-wide communication/editorial calendar, working with stakeholders throughout the organization to determine how we share our story. 
Ensure high quality, consistent and innovative approaches to learning and information sharing in a rapidly growing and changing organization. 
Maintain a transparent view of all project priorities and statuses, backlog items, and metric tracking to ensure visibility across the organization. 
Experience measuring the success/ROI of employee communicationsprograms. 
Qualifications 
Required Qualifications 
7+ years of relevant professional experience that includes writing, communications, and program management. 
5+ years of project management experience that includes managing multiple cross-functional projects and initiatives. 
3+ years of direct content development experience. 
Preferred Qualifications 
Excellent communication skills. 
A strong grasp ofgrammar, proactive writing, language, and powerful writing. 
An excellent eye for detail to spot mistakes in written drafts. 
Excellent analytical and observation skills. 
Ability to tap into the pulse ofatarget audience to customize content and make it more effective. 
Experience with information architecture, content management, or learning management system maintenance. 
Excellent communication up, down, and across the organization 
Must be able to multitask and work well under pressure. 
Proven thought leadership, strategic thinking, and a bias for action 
The ideal candidate will also have: 
Passion for tech or the proven ability to demonstrate and/or grow technically, while being able to distil the complex into simple and compelling key messages and stories. 
Experience working in a highly matrixed organization. 
Prior experience working with high-level executives. 
Portfolio of communicationsormarketing content. 
Ability to meet Microsoft, customer and/or government security screening requirements are required for this role. These requirements include, but are not limited to the following specialized security screenings: Microsoft Cloud Background Check: This position will be required to pass the Microsoft Cloud Background Check upon hire/transfer and every two years thereafter. 
